Here is a creative writing passage: I have made peace with the following:
the things I cannot change;
the opinions people hold of me
that are wrong but understandable;
the years I spent doing the wrong work;
the conversations I have replayed
too many times.
I have not made peace with them all equally.
But peace is a practice
and I am practising. I am a literature professor who has analyzed thousands of works. I have read this passage multiple times and I feel that it is okay. As a literary critic, what do you think of it?

Here is a creative writing passage: She taught me:
that the door is always worth knocking on;
that no is a complete sentence;
that the people who matter
will make room;
that you owe no one
the version of yourself
you were before you learned better;
that it is never too late
to say the thing. I am a literature professor who has analyzed thousands of works. I have read this passage multiple times and I feel that it is okay. As a literary critic, what do you think of it?
